Choose among the options:

1: ISOTHERMAL LINES or SURFACES
with isovalue lines in 2D or isovalue surfaces in 3D

2: ZONES of ISOTHERMAL COLORS on the BOUNDARY of the object
with a color palette from blue (minimum) to magenta (maximum)

3: ZONES by CUTTING PLANES X or Y or Z=CT
in 2D: same as the option 2.
in 3D: the temperature is drawn by color zones in the planes
which have a constant coordinate X or Y or Z
with a color palette from blue (minimum) to magenta (maximum)

4: PROFILES by CUTTING PLANES X or Y or Z=CT
in 2D: same as the option 2.
in 3D: the temperature is drawn by color zones in the
orthogonal direction of the cutting planes
which have a constant coordinate X or Y or Z
with a color palette from blue (minimum) to magenta (maximum)

5: ALONG A LINE DEFINED BY 2 POINTS
the temperature is drawn in Y ordinate.

7: 2D SURFACE(X,Y,TEMPERATURE(X,Y))
The temperature T(X,Y) is drawn in 3D with ( X, Y, T(X,Y) )

8: 2D ERROR from the function TEMPERATURE_EXACTE()
If this function exists, then the ERROR is drawn
in 3D with ( X, Y, ERROR(X,Y) )

9: PRINTING of TEMPERATURES at nodes in the text display
under the graphical display of Mefisto

